      "\n  have h₁ : l.count x = (smaller pivot l).count x + (larger pivot l).count x := by\n    have h₂ : l.count x = (l.filter (fun y => y ≤ pivot)).count x + (l.filter (fun y => pivot < y)).count x := by\n      have h₃ : l.count x = (l.filter (fun y => y ≤ pivot) ++ l.filter (fun y => pivot < y)).count x := by\n        have h₄ : l.filter (fun y => y ≤ pivot) ++ l.filter (fun y => pivot < y) = l := by\n          apply List.ext_get\n          intro i hi\n          simp only [List.mem_filter, List.mem_append, exists_prop]\n          have h₅ : l.get ⟨i, hi⟩ ≤ pivot ∨ pivot < l.get ⟨i, hi⟩ := by\n            have h₆ : l.get ⟨i, hi⟩ ≤ pivot ∨ pivot < l.get ⟨i, hi⟩ := by\n              cases' lt_or_le (l.get ⟨i, hi⟩) pivot with h₆ h₆\n              · exact Or.inr (by linarith)\n              · exact Or.inl h₆\n            exact h₆\n          cases' h₅ with h₅ h₅\n          · -- Case: l.get ⟨i, hi⟩ ≤ pivot\n            simp [h₅]\n            <;>\n            (try decide) <;>\n            (try omega) <;>\n            (try aesop) <;>\n            (try simp_all [List.get]) <;>\n            (try norm_num) <;>\n            (try linarith)\n          · -- Case: pivot < l.get ⟨i, hi⟩\n            simp [h₅]\n            <;>\n            (try decide) <;>\n            (try omega) <;>\n            (try aesop) <;>\n            (try simp_all [List.get]) <;>\n            (try norm_num) <;>\n            (try linarith)\n        rw [h₄]\n        <;>\n        simp [List.count_append]\n      rw [h₃]\n      simp [List.count_append]\n    have h₅ : (l.filter (fun y => y ≤ pivot)).count x = (smaller pivot l).count x := by\n      simp [smaller]\n    have h₆ : (l.filter (fun y => pivot < y)).count x = (larger pivot l).count x := by\n      simp [larger]\n    rw [h₅, h₆] at h₂\n    linarith\n  exact h₁",
      "\n  have h : l.count x = (l.filter (fun y => y ≤ pivot)).count x + (l.filter (fun y => pivot < y)).count x := by\n    have h₁ : l = (l.filter (fun y => y ≤ pivot)) ++ (l.filter (fun y => pivot < y)) := by\n      have h₂ : (l.filter (fun y => y ≤ pivot)) ++ (l.filter (fun y => pivot < y)) = l.filter (fun y => y ≤ pivot ∨ pivot < y) := by\n        rw [List.filter_add_filter_neg]\n        <;>\n        (try simp_all [not_le])\n        <;>\n        (try tauto)\n      have h₃ : l.filter (fun y => y ≤ pivot ∨ pivot < y) = l := by\n        apply List.filter_true_of_mem\n        intro y hy\n        by_cases h₄ : y ≤ pivot\n        · exact Or.inl h₄\n        · have h₅ : pivot < y := by\n            have h₆ : ¬(y ≤ pivot) := h₄\n            have h₇ : pivot < y := by\n              contrapose! h₆\n              exact le_of_not_gt h₆\n            exact h₇\n          exact Or.inr h₅\n      rw [h₂, h₃]\n    rw [h₁]\n    rw [List.count_append]\n  have h₂ : smaller pivot l = l.filter (fun y => y ≤ pivot) := by\n    simp [smaller]\n  have h₃ : larger pivot l = l.filter (fun y => pivot < y) := by\n    simp [larger]\n  rw [h₂, h₃] at *\n  linarith",
      "",
      "\n  have h₁ : (l.count x) = (smaller pivot l).count x + (larger pivot l).count x := by\n    have h₂ : ∀ (l : List α), (l.count x) = (smaller pivot l).count x + (larger pivot l).count x := by\n      intro l\n      induction l with\n      | nil =>\n        simp [smaller, larger]\n      | cons h t ih =>\n        simp [smaller, larger, List.count_cons, List.mem_filter] at ih ⊢\n        cases' lt_trichotomy h x with h₃ h₃\n        · -- Case: h < x\n          cases' lt_trichotomy x pivot with h₄ h₄\n          · -- Subcase: x < pivot\n            simp [h₃, h₄]\n            <;> simp_all [List.count_cons, List.mem_filter]\n            <;> omega\n          · -- Subcase: x = pivot or x > pivot\n            cases' h₄ with h₄ h₄\n            · -- Subsubcase: x = pivot\n              simp [h₃, h₄]\n              <;> simp_all [List.count_cons, List.mem_filter]\n              <;> omega\n            · -- Subsubcase: x > pivot\n              simp [h₃, h₄]\n              <;> simp_all [List.count_cons, List.mem_filter]\n              <;> omega\n        · -- Case: h = x\n          cases' lt_trichotomy x pivot with h₄ h₄\n          · -- Subcase: x < pivot\n            simp [h₃, h₄]\n            <;> simp_all [List.count_cons, List.mem_filter]\n            <;> omega\n          · -- Subcase: x = pivot or x > pivot\n            cases' h₄ with h₄ h₄\n            · -- Subsubcase: x = pivot\n              simp [h₃, h₄]\n              <;> simp_all [List.count_cons, List.mem_filter]\n              <;> omega\n            · -- Subsubcase: x > pivot\n              simp [h₃, h₄]\n              <;> simp_all [List.count_cons, List.mem_filter]\n              <;> omega\n        · -- Case: h > x\n          cases' lt_trichotomy x pivot with h₄ h₄\n          · -- Subcase: x < pivot\n            simp [h₃, h₄]\n            <;> simp_all [List.count_cons, List.mem_filter]\n            <;> omega\n          · -- Subcase: x = pivot or x > pivot\n            cases' h₄ with h₄ h₄\n            · -- Subsubcase: x = pivot\n              simp [h₃, h₄]\n              <;> simp_all [List.count_cons, List.mem_filter]\n              <;> omega\n            · -- Subsubcase: x > pivot\n              simp [h₃, h₄]\n              <;> simp_all [List.count_cons, List.mem_filter]\n              <;> omega\n    exact h₂ l\n  exact h₁",
      "\n   - If `a ≤ pivot`, then `a` is in `smaller pivot l`, but not in `larger`.\n   - If `a > pivot`, then `a` is in `larger pivot l`, but not in `smaller`.\n2. `a ≠ x`: \n   - The counts of `x` are unchanged in this case.\n\nBut perhaps it's better to consider cases based on whether `a ≤ pivot` or not.\n\n**Case 1:** Suppose `a ≤ pivot`.\nThen:\n- `smaller pivot l = a :: smaller pivot l'`, because `a ≤ pivot`.\n- `larger pivot l = larger pivot l'`, because `¬ (pivot < a)`.\n\nNow, we need to evaluate `count x l = count x (a :: l')`.\n\nWe have two subcases:\n1. `x = a`: Then `count x l = 1 + l'.count x`.\n   - Now, `smaller pivot l = a :: smaller pivot l'`, so `(smaller pivot l).count x = 1 + (smaller pivot l').count x`.\n   - `larger pivot l = larger pivot l'`, so `(larger pivot l).count x = (larger pivot l').count x`.\n   - By the inductive hypothesis, `l'.count x = (smaller pivot l').count x + (larger pivot l').count x`.\n   - Thus, `(smaller pivot l).count x + (larger pivot l).count x = 1 + (smaller pivot l').count x + (larger pivot l').count x = 1 + l'.count x = l.count x`.\n\n2. `x ≠ a`: Then `count x l = l'.count x`.\n   - `(smaller pivot l).count x = (smaller pivot l').count x`.\n   - `(larger pivot l).count x = (larger pivot l').count x`.\n   - By the inductive hypothesis, `l'.count x = (smaller pivot l').count x + (larger pivot l').count x = (smaller pivot l).count x + (larger pivot l).count x`.\n\n**Case 2:** Suppose `a > pivot`.\nThen:\n- `smaller pivot l = smaller pivot l'`, because `¬ (a ≤ pivot)`.\n- `larger pivot l = a :: larger pivot l'`, because `a > pivot`.\n\nAgain, two subcases:\n1. `x = a`: \n   - `count x l = 1 + l'.count x`.\n   - `(smaller pivot l).count x = (smaller pivot l').count x`.\n   - `(larger pivot l).count x = 1 + (larger pivot l').count x`.\n   - Inductive hypothesis: `l'.count x = (smaller pivot l').count x + (larger pivot l').count x`.\n   - Therefore, the sum is `(smaller pivot l').count x + 1 + (larger pivot l').count x = 1 + l'.count x`.\n\n2. `x ≠ a`:\n   - `count x l = l'.count x`.\n   - `(smaller pivot l).count x = (smaller pivot l').count x`.\n   - `(larger pivot l).count x = (larger pivot l').count x`.\n   - Inductive hypothesis again gives the result.\n\n### Step 7: Abstract Plan\n\n1. **Base Case:** Prove for the empty list.\n2. **Inductive Step:** For `a :: l'`, split into cases `a ≤ pivot` or `a > pivot`.\n   - In each case, split further into whether `x = a` or not.\n   - Use the inductive hypothesis to simplify.\n3. Use Lean's `cases` to split on whether `a ≤ pivot` and `x = a`, etc.\n\nHowever, perhaps we can prove a more general statement that `count x l = count x (filter p l) + count x (filter (¬·p) l)` for any decidable predicate `p`. \n\nBut actually, no, because if",
